author: Inside Edition
description: A London Sunday Times reporter says 24 hours before the escalator President Donald Trump and First Lady Melania were on at the United Nations building Tuesday suddenly stopped, UN staff members joked that they may turn off the escalators so the president would have to walk up the stairs. Inside Edition spoke with the Sunday Times reporter Katy Balls. UN officials are now pointing at one man, claiming he could have triggered the emergency brake by mistake.
title: Was The UN Escalator President Trump Was On Sabotaged?

author: Inside Edition
description: Jimmy Kimmel became emotional as he addressed the controversy that led to his suspension: the comments he made about Charlie Kirk's shooter. His eyes welled up again as he paid tribute to Kirk's widow Erika. The reviews for Kimmel's comeback are mostly positive. For Turning Point USA, the conservative organization founded by Charlie Kirk, it wasn't good enough. President Donald Trump also lashed out, slamming ABC's decision to bring Kimmel back. Meanwhile, Kimmel's monologue is a hit on YouTube.
title: Jimmy Kimmel's Return To Late Night Met With Mostly Positive Reviews

author: Inside Edition
description: Hamburger Helper was a budget-friendly way to feed the entire family. It was first introduced in 1971 and in the decades that have passed, it's been seen as a forgotten food from a bygone times. Now, with the price of beef at an all time high, families are reaching for Hamburger Helper to help stretch their dollars. Chef Jeffrey Eisner showed Inside Edition some inexpensive ways to make Hamburger Helper healthier.
title: More Families Buying 'Hamberger Helper' Amid Rising Cost Of Beef

author: Inside Edition
description: These real-life golden bachelorettes are ready for their second act. This group of older women are looking for life partners. Dating strategist Kimmy Seltzer says many people just need a boost to get back out there. Seltzer is hosting a dating retreat and Inside Edition was there as the woman got their mojo back. The women were treated to makeovers, photoshoots and a dance lesson. They also got to meet real-life golden bachelors.
title: These Women Prove It's Never Too Late To Find Love

author: Inside Edition
description: In June 2024, Lulu Gribbin was attacked by a shark on Florida's Gulf Coast. She was rushed to the hospital with devastating injuries, losing her left hand and right leg.
title: Teen Relearns Basic Tasks After Shark Attack Injuries #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: While Caleb McCoy was out for a jog in North Carolina's Smoky Mountains, a young black bear began trailing him. Desperate for the bear to leave, McCoy splashed the animal with water as he yelled to fellow hikers for a hand. With the bear refusing to scram, McCoy upped the ante by threatening the creature with a three-foot-stick. Despite the show of force, the nosy intruder still wouldn't leave. McCoy spoke with Inside Edition's Les Trent.
title: Bear Trails Man In Smoky Mountains

author: Inside Edition
description: A police officer in Alaska rushed to a car that wouldn’t stop honking, fearing that it could be someone in distress. But when the cop arrived, it turned out to be something he didn’t expect. Check out what it was that made all the noise in the neighborhood!
title: What Made This Car Honk Uncontrollably?

author: Inside Edition
description: At age 16, Courtney Stodden’s marriage to 51-year-old actor Doug Hutchinson sent shockwaves across the country.
title: Courtney Stodden Says She Was Groomed #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A teenager who inspired millions of followers with her brave fight against cancer has died. Zuza Beine documented her daily life with acute myeloid leukemia on social media, garnering millions of viewers who witnessed her daily achievements and struggles. Zuza was first diagnosed when she was 3 years old. More than a decade later it had taken over her life, but more than anything, she wanted a normal childhood. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Influencer Zuza Beine Dies At 14 After Long Struggle With Leukemia

author: Inside Edition
description: Scientists have been sounding the alarm on climate change for years because of things like this. It's a glacier in Switzerland and researchers say it's dying. Those who keep an eye on it say it lost 20 feet in the past year, which is a rapid melt. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Swiss Glacier Loses 20 Feet in a Year in What Experts Call Environmental Crisis

author: Inside Edition
description: This vest promises to cushion falls with a motion-triggered airbag system. But does it always work? Steven Fabian tried it out.
title: Steven Fabian Describes Anti-Fall Vest Experience #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: The Trump administration claimed Monday that Tylenol can lead to autism. Many doctors have spoken out saying that is not true.
title: Doctors Speak Out About Tylenol Claims #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Worry etched comic Drew Lynch's face as people in the club raced to help 83-year-old Richard Wende.
title: Man Saved From Massive Heart Attack At Comedy Show #shorts
